    "The closure phases (ψ C), log closure amplitudes (ln A C), closure trace phases and closure trace log amplitudes T, the latter two of which are novel diagnostics described in detail by Broderick & Pesce (2020), are independent of station-based gain errors, but are sensitive to systematic non-closing systematic errors.",
    "Figure B.1 shows the normalized distributions of the differences in the closure quantities between bands (band 1 -band 2, band 3 -band 4), polarizations (RR-LL), as well as the distributions of the trivial closure quantities derived from triangles or quadrangles with at least two co-located stations.",
    "In an ideal scenario where polarimetric leakages are absent, the differences in closure quantities between bands and polarizations, as well as the trivial closure quantities, is expected to follow a normal distribution with a mean value of zero.",
    "The presence of non-closing systematic errors can lead to deviations from the expected normal distribution, as can be seen for the blue histograms in Fig.",
